---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="Our Story">
  <h1>Our Story</h1>
  <p class="label">How and why Project Cognify began</p>

  <div class="prose">
    <h2>It Started With a Simple Question</h2>
    <p>
      One night, two of our founders stayed up until 2:00 a.m. playing a newly
      released Roblox update. Hours flew by without anyone noticing. The next
      day, one question kept coming up:
    </p>
    <blockquote class="pullquote">
      Why is it so easy to spend hours focused on a game, yet so difficult to
      spend thirty minutes focused on homework?
    </blockquote>
    <p>
      The more we talked about it, the more we realized this wasn't just our
      experience. It was something many students seemed to struggle with.
    </p>
    <p>Instead of guessing at the answer, we decided to investigate it.</p>
    <p>That's how Project Cognify began.</p>

    <h2>Why We're Doing This</h2>
    <p>
      Like most students, we've experienced how difficult it can be to stay
      focused when there are so many distractions competing for our attention.
      Phones, notifications, social media, games, and endless content are all
      designed to keep us engaged.
    </p>
    <p>Most solutions focus on removing distractions.</p>
    <p>We wanted to explore a different question.</p>
    <blockquote class="pullquote">
      What if the same psychology that keeps us engaged could be used to help us
      stay focused on things that matter?
    </blockquote>
    <p>We don't know if that's possible yet.</p>
    <p>That's exactly what we're trying to find out.</p>

    <h2>Our Goal</h2>
    <p>Project Cognify isn't about building another productivity app.</p>
    <p>
      Our goal is to better understand how students focus, what motivates them,
      and whether technology can become part of the solution instead of part of
      the problem.
    </p>
    <p>We believe good ideas should be supported by evidence.</p>
    <p>
      That's why we're spending months researching before we build anything.
    </p>

    <h2>How We're Approaching It</h2>
    <p>Instead of starting with a solution, we're starting with questions.</p>
    <p>
      We're reviewing academic research, surveying students, conducting
      interviews, and analyzing what we learn before designing a prototype.
    </p>
    <p>If the evidence supports our original idea, we'll keep building.</p>
    <p>If the evidence points us somewhere else, we'll change course.</p>
    <p>We believe that's how meaningful innovation happens.</p>

    <h2>What We Hope Happens</h2>
    <p>We don't expect to have all the answers.</p>
    <p>In fact, we hope this project changes our thinking along the way.</p>
    <p>
      Whether our original hypothesis turns out to be right or wrong, we'll
      share what we learn and continue improving our ideas.
    </p>
    <p>
      If Project Cognify helps even a few students better understand their own
      focus and motivation, we'll consider that a success.
    </p>

    <h2>Why We're Sharing Our Journey</h2>
    <p>Most projects only show the finished product.</p>
    <p>We wanted to do something different.</p>
    <p>
      This website is where we'll document everything along the way, including
      our research, ideas, prototypes, successes, mistakes, and lessons learned.
    </p>
    <p>
      Because we believe the journey is just as important as the destination.
    </p>

    <h2>A Note From the Team</h2>
    <p>
      We're just three high school students who became curious about a problem
      we experience every day.
    </p>
    <p>We don't have all the answers.</p>
    <p>
      But we're excited to ask good questions, follow the evidence, and see
      where it leads.
    </p>
    <p>Thanks for following our journey.</p>

    <p class="closing">
      Curiosity started this project. Research is shaping it. We hope it helps
      students everywhere.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .pullquote {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--foreground);
    margin: 1.75rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.1rem;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--primary);
  }

  .prose h2 {
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .closing {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--muted-foreground);
  }
</style>
